        <h2>Director-band mortgage, structured right.</h2>
        <p>Director of Product at a publicly traded software company, three-year tenure, $215K base salary, $58K annual RSU vest (mostly time-based), $35K annual cash bonus on a consistent two-year history, and ESPP participation adding $7,500 to W-2 box 1. The first lender pulled just the base salary from the paystub, didn&rsquo;t ask about RSUs, treated the bonus as discretionary, and missed the ESPP entirely. Their offer: $720K maximum loan. We pulled the grant letter (the executive&rsquo;s first), the vesting schedule, the W-2s showing the two-year bonus history with the ESPP discount embedded, and the brokerage statements with vested share values. Ran the Fannie Mae 200-day moving average for RSU income calculation. Two-year bonus average added properly. ESPP discount documented as ongoing W-2 component. Total qualifying income: $315K. Approved at $1.05M for a Doral home with a pool. Closed in 28 days. The Director tier is the most consistently under-quoted in corporate-executive mortgages &mdash; not because the comp is exotic, but because lenders trained on entry-level W-2 underwriting don&rsquo;t pull the equity-comp pieces.</p>
